like Blue Skies or Black Skies app view, because

00:14:47.560 --> 00:14:52.030
we believe that social media data can already incubate so many

00:14:52.030 --> 00:14:56.040
applications that deal with followers, likes, and posts.

00:14:56.120 --> 00:14:58.480
So I think it's in a public interest to have an

00:14:58.500 --> 00:15:02.190
app view that can serve all these different apps that we already

00:15:02.190 --> 00:15:03.040
have today.

00:15:03.120 --> 00:15:06.910
But we're also looking at a talk to chat yesterday running

00:15:06.910 --> 00:15:11.920
, for example, slices or -- sorry -- constellation mirrors or

00:15:11.920 --> 00:15:14.030
gazetteers for ATGeo projects.

00:15:14.120 --> 00:15:17.980
So if you have something that you think is public infrastructure or

00:15:17.980 --> 00:15:21.040
should be public infrastructure, come talk to us.

00:15:21.120 --> 00:15:23.350
And we'll see if we can make it happen and make

00:15:23.430 --> 00:15:26.030
it run for everybody on our infrastructure.

00:15:26.120 --> 00:15:33.630
In parallel, we'll start working on compliance pipelines for developers

00:15:33.630 --> 00:15:33.960
.

00:15:34.120 --> 00:15:37.080
Ultimately, the goal is to have a sort of shared moderation

00:15:37.290 --> 00:15:40.040
experience for app developers that share certain lexicons.

00:15:40.120 --> 00:15:47.310
And we're currently talking to Roost over there about integrating

00:15:47.320 --> 00:15:49.040
Co-op and Osprey for this.

00:15:49.120 --> 00:15:54.900
So, yeah, this will be the step after the next

00:15:55.100 --> 00:15:56.040
step.

00:15:56.120 --> 00:15:59.590
EuroSky is also participating in two European tenders right

00:15:59.610 --> 00:16:00.020
now.

00:16:00.120 --> 00:16:04.180
One is called Social Pets, and it will implement a

00:16:04.180 --> 00:16:07.710
couple of things, one of which is a privacy-pres

00:16:07.710 --> 00:16:13.030
erving training and inference for decentralized social media recommender algorithms.

00:16:13.120 --> 00:16:16.650
It will also -- I'm reading this because I cannot remember

00:16:16.660 --> 00:16:20.480
it -- the other one is quantum-resistant privacy-

00:16:20.490 --> 00:16:23.080
preserving zero-knowledge credentials for age-gating

00:16:23.140 --> 00:16:26.040
, reputation, and anti-abuse without tracking.

00:16:26.120 --> 00:16:29.090
And the last one will be privacy-preserving trust and

00:16:29.190 --> 00:16:33.780
safety collaboration across relays and servers via multiparty computation

00:16:33.900 --> 00:16:34.040
.

00:16:34.120 --> 00:16:41.120
This will let different instances in the network signal abuse signals to

00:16:41.120 --> 00:16:44.040
each other without exposing private data.

00:16:44.120 --> 00:16:46.040
We're hoping to hear from that.

00:16:46.120 --> 00:16:48.040
It's an EU Horizon grant.

00:16:48.120 --> 00:16:52.680
These things take months to apply for, and then it takes

00:16:52.680 --> 00:16:56.440
the double amount of months for them to decide whether you get

00:16:56.440 --> 00:16:57.040
it or not.

00:16:57.120 --> 00:16:59.040
So, we've been waiting for six months.

00:16:59.120 --> 00:17:00.040
This would be awesome.

00:17:00.120 --> 00:17:03.800
The other tender we're currently working on with TU Dres

00:17:03.800 --> 00:17:07.490
den, and with the advisory of GreenEarth, namely

00:17:07.490 --> 00:17:10.720
Rene Diresta, Glenn Weil, and Jonathan Stray

00:17:10.720 --> 00:17:11.030
.

00:17:11.120 --> 00:17:14.650
And the goal with this one will be to develop a production

00:17:14.690 --> 00:17:19.510
pro-social feed, basically a bridging algorithm that creates

00:17:19.710 --> 00:17:22.020
engagement without polarization.

00:17:22.120 --> 00:17:26.180
And that will then be open sourced and incorporated into our

00:17:26.190 --> 00:17:30.840
Eurosky infrastructure and thus be made available to anyone who builds

00:17:30.900 --> 00:17:36.040
on Eurosky and who wants to have a good recommender

00:17:36.040 --> 00:17:41.000
algorithm in their app.

00:17:41.120 --> 00:17:44.040
Yeah, we started this talk with infrastructure being captured.

00:17:44.120 --> 00:17:47.670
So, how do we make sure that Eurosky cannot be

00:17:47.670 --> 00:17:50.040
captured and screw us all?

00:17:50.120 --> 00:17:53.040
Well, Ivan kind of laid it out already.

00:17:53.120 --> 00:17:57.640
The mentioned components are all embedded in this nonprofit, the Mod

00:17:57.640 --> 00:18:01.070
al Foundation, and that's not because we couldn't raise

00:18:01.070 --> 00:18:05.640
capital, but because public infrastructure must not be embedded in like

00:18:05.640 --> 00:18:11.660
one company whose incentives could diverge from the ecosystem's needs

00:18:11.660 --> 00:18:12.040
.

00:18:12.120 --> 00:18:15.990
And this is not a criticism of anyone building in this space

00:18:15.990 --> 00:18:17.030
in that way.

00:18:17.110 --> 00:18:20.040
I think it's just good infrastructure design.

00:18:20.120 --> 00:18:24.020
Basically, the same logic as public broadcasting.

00:18:24.120 --> 00:18:27.040
So, no single point of capture.

00:18:27.120 --> 00:18:28.040
And that includes us.

00:18:28.120 --> 00:18:31.040
So, we're making ourselves accountable to the mission.

00:18:31.120 --> 00:18:35.250
And we can't be sold from under the people who depend

00:18:35.280 --> 00:18:36.030
on it.

00:18:36.120 --> 00:18:40.150
The business model, we don't need to talk about that

00:18:40.160 --> 00:18:41.030
, right?

00:18:41.150 --> 00:18:46.030
Well, okay.

00:18:46.120 --> 00:18:50.660
It will be grants for now and funding by the EU later

00:18:50.660 --> 00:18:51.030
.

00:18:51.120 --> 00:18:55.610
Furthermore, we're looking at services running on our infrastructure that

00:18:55.610 --> 00:18:59.040
can then maybe back finance our expenses.

00:18:59.120 --> 00:19:03.020
That is the general direction for now.

00:19:03.120 --> 00:19:05.610
And like I said, at our launch event in November last

00:19:05.690 --> 00:19:08.320
year, we'll be interoperable with all of you

00:19:08.320 --> 00:19:12.680
all, all of the other people building on this right now

00:19:12.680 --> 00:19:13.030
.

00:19:13.120 --> 00:19:15.040
We'll even bridge to Mastodon.

00:19:15.120 --> 00:19:18.080
So, we're not asking anyone to choose any of these

00:19:18.090 --> 00:19:19.020
platforms.

00:19:19.120 --> 00:19:23.020
We're just adding a layer that makes the whole network stronger

00:19:23.020 --> 00:19:28.740
and more legally resilient, more accessible to builders who need European

00:19:28.740 --> 00:19:30.030
compliance.

00:19:30.120 --> 00:19:32.910
If you want to meet us, this will be the next

00:19:32.910 --> 00:19:34.020
opportunity.

00:19:34.120 --> 00:19:35.040
Yes.

00:19:35.120 --> 00:19:37.220
We'll be in Amsterdam, June 4th, 5th

00:19:37.230 --> 00:19:38.040
, and 6th of June.

00:19:38.120 --> 00:19:40.740
And we're doing this together with New Public, who is

00:19:40.740 --> 00:19:42.020
presented over there.

00:19:42.120 --> 00:19:45.080
Then, of course, the AtmosphereConf, Safe

00:19:45.240 --> 00:19:47.590
Social, the FETI Forum, and the Z

00:19:47.590 --> 00:19:52.040
DF, which is a public broadcaster from Germany.

00:19:52.120 --> 00:19:54.040
And with that, I thank you.

00:19:54.120 --> 00:19:56.820
And we have, like I anticipated, 10 minutes for questions

00:19:56.820 --> 00:19:57.040
.

00:19:57.120 --> 00:19:58.040
Excellent.

